root: ^So here's how I became a software engineer.
^But , first guess what I majored in.

s: ^No one cares what you majored in

g-0: ^While I didn't study compsci formally, since I know I was dropping out at 22 or so anyway, I skipped my college classes and worked on games.
^The very first thing I made, was a beat box/noise maker called BeatQuest. I totally had no idea a decade or so later I'd be a software engineer.
^This is a Godot project, but I've learned the vast majority of my programing with Unity.
